I guess this is a long way of saying, if you want to put Wikipedia articles on a map, or otherwise need GeoJSON for Wikipedia articles for a particular location, take a look at[wikigeo.js](http://edsu.github.io/wikigeo/). If you do, and have ideas for making it better, please let me know. Oh, by the way you can `npm install[wikigeo](https://npmjs.org/package/wikigeo)` and use it from [Node.js](http://nodejs.org).

I guess JavaScript, HTML5, NodeJS, CoffeeScript are like my midlife crisis…my red sports car. But maybe being the old guy, and losing my edge isn’t really so bad?

> I’m losing my edge  
