![](https://chart.googleapis.com/chart?chs=300x200&cht=v&chd=t:86.7469879518,72.2891566265,19.2771084337,49,16,15,15&chco=77FF77,7777FF,FF7777&chdl=xISBN|ThingISBN|OpenLibrary&chtt=Neuromancer (0441569595))Because of some work I’ve been doing helping out at[Gluejar](http://gluejar.com) I became curious about the coverage of these three FRBR workset APIs. What sort of overlap is there between them? I wrote a little script[worksvenn.py](https://github.com/edsu/worksvenn/blob/master/worksvenn.py)that takes one or more ISBNs as input, looks them up in the OpenLibrary, LibraryThing and OCLC APIs, and then outputs the resulting data with a Venn diagram using the[Google Chart API](http://code.google.com/apis/chart/image/docs/gallery/venn%5Fcharts.html).

It’s interesting to see that each service has unique results. You can see these when you run `worksvenn.py` on the command line:

